@startuml ct_data_observability
' ============================================================
' Title:     nasim — Observability Data Structures
' Boundary:  NASIM Application — WireLogRepository (emit-only observability data)
' Purpose:   Data models for structured logging, metrics, and trace correlation
' Milestone: v1.0
' Version:   1.0.0
' Source:    docs/audit/audit.2026.06.20.logging.observability.car.md
' Review:    —
' Note:      Emit-only per tenas pattern. Structured records go to stdout.
'            Metrics exposed via /metrics pull endpoint.
'            OTel export is optional (behind feature flag).
' ============================================================

title nasim — Observability Data Structures

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

package "Observability Data" #E3F2FD {

    class LogRecord <<dataclass>> {
        + record_id : str
        + timestamp : str
        + level : LogLevel
        + logger_name : str
        + message : str
        + trace_id : str
        + span_id : str
        + parent_span_id : str
        + session_id : str
        + turn_number : int
        + extra : dict
        + redacted : bool
    }

    class LogLevel <<enumeration>> {
        TRACE
        DEBUG
        INFO
        WARNING
        ERROR
        CRITICAL
    }

    class MetricPoint <<dataclass>> {
        + name : str
        + type : MetricType
        + value : float
        + labels : dict
        + timestamp : float
    }

    class MetricType <<enumeration>> {
        COUNTER
        GAUGE
        HISTOGRAM
        SUMMARY
    }

    class TraceContext <<dataclass>> {
        + trace_id : str
        + span_id : str
        + parent_span_id : str
        + session_id : str
        + turn_number : int
        + operation_name : str
        + start_time : float
        + end_time : float
        + status : str
    }

    class ObservabilityConfig <<dataclass>> {
        + log_level : LogLevel
        + log_format : str
        + structured_enabled : bool
        + wire_enabled : bool
        + redact_enabled : bool
        + redact_patterns : list[str]
        + metrics_enabled : bool
        + otel_enabled : bool
        + otel_endpoint : str
        + sampling_rate : float
    }

    class RedactionRule <<dataclass>> {
        + pattern : str
        + replacement : str
        + scope : str
        + enabled : bool
    }
}

note bottom of LogRecord
  Every structured log record carries correlation ids.
  trace_id links to TraceContext for end-to-end correlation.
  session_id and turn_number enable wire<->structured cross-ref.
  extra holds domain-specific key-value pairs (model, tokens, etc).
end note

note bottom of MetricPoint
  Prometheus-compatible metric points.
  name follows convention: nasim_<metric>[_<unit>]
  labels are low-cardinality (model, provider, tool, success).
  HISTOGRAM includes _bucket, _sum, _count suffixes.
end note

note bottom of TraceContext
  Request-scoped trace context bound via contextvars.
  trace_id is root (per CLI turn or HTTP request).
  span_id is current operation; parent_span_id is caller.
  Shared with OTel when otel feature enabled.
end note

note right of ObservabilityConfig
  Loaded from layered config (global → project → env → CLI).
  Controls emission behavior: what, how much, how safe.
  Wire log has separate enabled flag (domain artifact).
end note

note right of RedactionRule
  Regex-based secret stripping before any emission.
  Global rules (env vars, keys) + per-project rules.
  Applied by LogRedactor to both structured and wire events.
end note

@enduml
